do n't let this one lousy book put you off robinson peter robinson has turned into a first-rate mystery writer . but he certainly was n't when he wrote this in 1989 . no amount of gorgeous yorkshire scenery can make up for an uninteresting cast of one-dimensional characters and an abrupt . out-of-left-field ending . skip this atypical entry and read his later inspector banks books -- they 're first rate and well deserving of all the acclaim and slew of awards he 's won . this is n't